[2026-07-03 06:18:36] darwin: cycle 24 -- fixed zero-width/bidi Unicode char stripping bug in output_sanitizer.el. The patterns for zero-width characters (U+200B/C/D, U+FEFF) and RTL override (U+202E) were written as plain strings without character class brackets, so they matched a literal multi-character sequence that never appears in real text -- individual zero-width chars were never stripped. Fixed by wrapping in [] character classes. Also expanded coverage: zero-width pattern now includes U+200E (LRM), U+200F (RLM), U+2060 (WJ), U+2061-2064 (invisible math operators); bidi pattern expanded from just U+202E to all 9 Unicode bidi controls (U+202A-E, U+2066-69) to prevent Trojan Source attacks. Changed \x to \u notation (cosmetic -- both produce identical strings in Emacs Lisp). Reviewer found 2 CRITICAL (incomplete bidi coverage, missing zero-width chars), 2 MAJOR (incorrect \xHH claim in task description -- Emacs regex doesn't support \xHH at all, \x is a Lisp string reader escape that reads all hex digits; no full pipeline test for zero-width chars), 3 MINOR (redundant single-element character class, mixed test missing bidi, no negative test for normal Unicode). All addressed: expanded both patterns, added full pipeline test, added normal Unicode preservation test, added mixed zero-width+bidi test. 13 new tests total (331 -> 344). All 344 tests pass. Committed f694bbc, pushed to remote.
[2026-07-03 06:52:48] darwin: cycle 25 -- extracted my-gptel--memory-parse-ollama-response from my-gptel--memory-call-ollama (memory_tools.el) for testability. Fixed two bugs discovered during extraction and review: (1) Error prefix inconsistency: 'Error parsing JSON:' started with 'Error ' (space) not 'Error:' (colon), so the caller's (string-prefix-p 'Error:' result) would NOT match -- JSON parse errors would be silently treated as valid content and written to MEMORIES.md. Changed to 'Error: parsing JSON:'. (2) Non-string content bypass: (and content (not (string-empty-p content))) did not check stringp. JSON false maps to :json-false (a symbol) in Emacs 30, which passes the 'and' check because string-empty-p returns nil for symbols (not an error). The symbol :json-false would be returned as content, crashing string-trim in the caller. Fixed by adding (stringp content) guard. Also fixed empty-content check: old (or (plist-get :content) ...) only caught nil, not empty strings. Added 10 tests: valid response, empty content, no message key, invalid JSON, empty string, nil content, multiline content, JSON false, numeric content, JSON null. Removed unused lexical variable 'dir' in test-memory-extract-from-existing-file. Reviewer found CRITICAL (non-string content bypass for :json-false), 2 MAJOR (missing non-string test cases, string-empty-p inconsistency across types), 2 MINOR (unused var, large error messages). All addressed. All 354 tests pass. Committed ec5c720, pushed to remote.
