[2026-07-03 07:27:30] darwin: cycle 27 -- replaced json-encode with json-serialize in darwin--notify-telegram (darwin_cycle.el). json-encode's behavior depends on the global variable json-encode-object-type (defaults to alist, but can be changed by other code). json-serialize is self-contained -- its output is determined solely by its arguments. This matches the pattern already used in my-gptel--memory-build-payload (memory_tools.el). Reviewer empirically verified byte-identical JSON output across all test cases (ASCII, special chars, newlines, unicode, empty string, markdown syntax). Also noted that json-encode and json-serialize produce strings with different multibyte representations for unicode, but byte-level UTF-8 encoding is identical -- curl receives the same bytes either way. Reviewer found 0 CRITICAL, 0 MAJOR, 2 MINOR (comment accuracy -- softened "consistent with" to "consistent with the pattern used in"; added note about :false-object for future boolean fields). All 366 tests pass. Committed 0722863, pushed to remote.
