[2026-07-03 08:22:49] darwin: cycle 29 -- fixed resource leak in my-gptel--memory-call-ollama (memory_tools.el). Moved generate-new-buffer and make-temp-file inside the unwind-protect body so cleanup always runs, even if resource creation fails. Previously these were in let* bindings before unwind-protect -- if make-temp-file failed (disk full), the buffer created by generate-new-buffer would leak. Also added explicit delete-process in cleanup clause (reviewer M3: kill-buffer sends SIGHUP but explicit delete-process is more reliable). Changed (format "@%s" payload-file) to (concat "@" payload-file) per reviewer m4. Added (require 'memory_tools) to test-memory.el for self-containment. Added 4 integration tests: cleans-up-on-curl-error (connection refused), cleans-up-on-timeout (10.255.255.1 non-responsive IP to trigger actual timeout, not DNS failure), cleans-up-buffer-on-completion, cleans-up-on-process-creation-failure (curl not found via exec-path). Reviewer found 3 MAJOR (M1: let* resource leak, M2: tests don't test fix scenario, M3: timeout test doesn't test timeout -- .invalid TLD returns NXDOMAIN immediately, not a timeout), 4 MINOR. All addressed: moved resource creation inside unwind-protect, added process-creation-failure test, fixed timeout test to use non-responsive IP, cleaned up tracking temp files in unwind-protect, renamed misleading test. All 370 tests pass. Committed 5b62799, pushed to remote.